<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="594" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[351,411,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">Adult</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[427,559,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[222,1368,1185,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[212,1378,1163,1931]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Adults of Hergovitsia.1a. H. longivirga n. sp., male (holotype, INU˗100024) 1b. ditto, female (paratype, INU˗1713C). 2a. H. magnifica, male (paratype, Malaysia, SAS. m˗1). 2b. ditto, female (paratype, Malaysia, SAS. fm˗2)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614957/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">Figs. 1a, 1b</figureCitation>
). Length of forewing 
<quantity box="[805,898,151,176]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="594" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 mm</quantity>
in male and female. Male (
<figureCitation box="[1204,1285,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[222,1368,1185,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[212,1378,1163,1931]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Adults of Hergovitsia.1a. H. longivirga n. sp., male (holotype, INU˗100024) 1b. ditto, female (paratype, INU˗1713C). 2a. H. magnifica, male (paratype, Malaysia, SAS. m˗1). 2b. ditto, female (paratype, Malaysia, SAS. fm˗2)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614957/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
): head white. Patagium, thorax and tegula white, mixed with brown scales. Forewing ground color pale gray, with one small dark discoidal spot; medial pale brown band diffused from discoidal area; apical area pale gray, with one dark brown spot in apex; dorsal area tinged with pale brown; cilia pale, mixed with pale brown scales. Hindwing sordid white, with deep recess from apex to vein Cu1; terminal area tinged with pale brown; cilia sordid white, mixed with pale brown scales. Abdomen white, with pale yellow anal tuft. Female (
<figureCitation box="[929,1015,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="1.[151,264,1948,1971]" captionTargetBox="[222,1368,1185,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[212,1378,1163,1931]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Adults of Hergovitsia.1a. H. longivirga n. sp., male (holotype, INU˗100024) 1b. ditto, female (paratype, INU˗1713C). 2a. H. magnifica, male (paratype, Malaysia, SAS. m˗1). 2b. ditto, female (paratype, Malaysia, SAS. fm˗2)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614957/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
): Head, patagium, thorax and tegula sordid white, mixed with brown scales. Forewing ground color pale brown˗gray, with one small dark discoidal spot and indistinct brown markings; pale costal band from medial to apex, with one dark spot in apex; pale gray terminal band distinct; cilia pale, mixed with pale brown scales. Hindwing brown, tinged with gray in basal area; cilia pale. Abdomen gray˗white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis box="[199,363,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[378,553,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1753,1776]" captionTargetBox="[248,1305,203,1734]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[191,1402,193,1734]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3–4. Genitalia of Hergovitsia longivirga n. sp. 2a. Male genitalia (paratype, INU˗1714C). 2b. Aedeagus. 2c. Detail of saccular process and saccus parts. 3. Female genitalia (paratype, INU 10020C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614959/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">Figs. 3a, 3b, 3c</figureCitation>
). Uncus slender, weakly waved, with a small apical spine. Tegumen triangular. Valva slender, almost eight times longer than uncus, heavily covered with hairs fully (
<figureCitation box="[1143,1227,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1753,1776]" captionTargetBox="[248,1305,203,1734]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[191,1402,193,1734]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3–4. Genitalia of Hergovitsia longivirga n. sp. 2a. Male genitalia (paratype, INU˗1714C). 2b. Aedeagus. 2c. Detail of saccular process and saccus parts. 3. Female genitalia (paratype, INU 10020C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614959/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
); saccular process irregularly rectangular, strongly sclerotized in edge, upper angle of apex with waved, 2 short and one long (2 times longer than short two), finger˗shaped projections, and lower angle of apex roundly angled with a weakly sclerotized, triangular spur ventrally; costal margin of saccular process bifurcated apically (
<figureCitation box="[1244,1332,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1753,1776]" captionTargetBox="[248,1305,203,1734]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[191,1402,193,1734]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3–4. Genitalia of Hergovitsia longivirga n. sp. 2a. Male genitalia (paratype, INU˗1714C). 2b. Aedeagus. 2c. Detail of saccular process and saccus parts. 3. Female genitalia (paratype, INU 10020C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614959/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">Fig. 3c</figureCitation>
). Saccus broadly U˗shaped (
<figureCitation box="[369,452,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1753,1776]" captionTargetBox="[248,1305,203,1734]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[191,1402,193,1734]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3–4. Genitalia of Hergovitsia longivirga n. sp. 2a. Male genitalia (paratype, INU˗1714C). 2b. Aedeagus. 2c. Detail of saccular process and saccus parts. 3. Female genitalia (paratype, INU 10020C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614959/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">Fig. 3c</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus stout, weakly sclerotized in apical half and vesica with one row of diverse sized spines, one strongly sclerotized irregular process, and two large spine˗shaped cornuti (
<figureCitation box="[1182,1265,727,752]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1753,1776]" captionTargetBox="[248,1305,203,1734]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[191,1402,193,1734]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3–4. Genitalia of Hergovitsia longivirga n. sp. 2a. Male genitalia (paratype, INU˗1714C). 2b. Aedeagus. 2c. Detail of saccular process and saccus parts. 3. Female genitalia (paratype, INU 10020C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614959/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis box="[199,394,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[412,486,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1753,1776]" captionTargetBox="[248,1305,203,1734]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[191,1402,193,1734]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3–4. Genitalia of Hergovitsia longivirga n. sp. 2a. Male genitalia (paratype, INU˗1714C). 2b. Aedeagus. 2c. Detail of saccular process and saccus parts. 3. Female genitalia (paratype, INU 10020C)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2614959/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Papillae anales weakly covered with setae. Ductus bursae straight, tube˗shaped, covered with short spines in weakly sclerotized area in 2/3 from ostium, and plate of long spines in membranous area near cervix of bursae. Corpus bursae ovoid, membranous, with one rounded signum in weakly sclerotized proximal half of bursae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
