<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="594" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,943,968]" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from the Latin, 
<emphasis box="[855,930,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">longus</emphasis>
(long) and 
<emphasis box="[1065,1123,944,967]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="594">virga</emphasis>
(broom), refers to the long and heavily covered with hairs of valva.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
